Pre-Game Insights: Denmark manager Kasper Hjulmand is expecting to have all 26 players at his disposal for Tuesday's Euro 2024 Group C finale against Serbia.
Thomas Delaney will likely take his seat on the bench as Morten Hjulmand and Pierre-Emile Hojbjerg excelled against England.
Victor Kristiansen struggled against Bukayo Saka, leading to Joakim Maehle potentially starting on the left and Alexander Bah taking up right wing-back duties.
Jannik Vestergaard is one of a few players one yellow card away from a ban, but should still start alongside Joachim Andersen and Andreas Christensen in defense.
